rComments: Tough grader and does not explain how to really improve. Difficulty understanding in class but she uses blackboard well. Over not awful but definatly not an amazing experience.
Such a sweet lady and very helpful! Very clear about what she wants and a good grader. I found it hard to understand in class, but made the best of it!
AMZING PROF. I took a first year course with her and I am now going to take a second year course with her. She is just the sweetest lady. Very clear in what she expects, always willing to help.

Dr. Sexton is honestly one of the most pleasant teachers I've had in my first year! She is so kind and helpful if you ask for clarification or help, and is a HUGE help for essays! Run them by her before you submit them (well before the due date) and she will guide you, show you your weak points and help you write a better essay! TAKE HER CLASS!!!!!

She is a very nice and kind professor, not intimidating at all. Very easy to go up and ask questions, as she is always willing to help. The course is easy, just have a clear understanding of the short stories. If you have an issue with the essays then just get them checked by her. She tries to guide you into the right path.

SHE IS THE BEST PROF I HAD. oh my God she is such a sweet heart. she inspired me alot and the fact that she's deaf but still pursuits her career shows me how nothing is impossible. she is like a mother to students she cares so much and she has the kindest heart ever. TAKE HER CLASS FOR SURE !!  she's so funny too !! :)

Professor Melanie is by far the best prof I have ever met. This lady is amazing. She's always willing to help you and also encourages you when she notice you are having great difficulties. I adore her personality. She is my inspiration.

Had her first year, and she's the sweetest lady you'll ever meet. Is always trying to make it easier for her students, always available, and loves to clarify any questions. You could barely tell she was completely deaf after the first class, and it's been a pleasure. Take her English class, she makes it interesting!

What a delightful prof! I'll admit to being initially wary to realize that she's deaf, but after the first class I barely noticed. She works with an interpreter so she can communicate when there are questions, but otherwise she's easy to understand and absolutely charming. Expectations are clear, if you attend and do the readings you'll do well.

Very sweet woman!  Thoroughly enjoyed the class and loved the amount of discussion on each story.  Feedback on assignments was in depth and incredibly useful and thoughtful.  Would definitely recommend!

She's still one of my favourite profs, and I'm not even studying english. Her exams and quizzes are easy if you pay attention, and if you do what she asks of you for the papers, you will get a good mark. She's hilarious, and her lectures are never boring!
I never liked english, but she made it interesting :) very good prof! I would recommend her to anybody.
She basically write what she lectures on and you should be good. Just don't have original thoughts of your own.

She is an excellent teacher! She is always willing to assist you in any way she can. She is hands down fantastic! You couldn't ask for a better professor. She actually teaches you. She is a respected teacher, and she is very much appreciated my students. She is hands down the best teacher I've had so far in two years!

What a wonderful professor!!! So compassionate and approachable. She is very passionate and ethusiastic about what she does. She is clear about everything and leaves nothing to ambiguity. She genuinely wants every st udent to do well.  Attend and participate in class and you will do well.

She is wonderful. She is personal in terms of knowing everyone's names, very observant, and most importantly extraordinary helpful for help if you ask for it. She will take you paper and turn it inside out if you send it to her a good week prior to the due date, send her revised version and she will do the same, and then get agreat mark in the end!

She was the best professor I have had!! English is my second language and my writing skills were not the best, I was too wordy and my vocabulary was a bit odd, but she put in so much time to help me cut down on useless words and showed me how to use the English language to say what I want to say clearly and concisely. I couldn't have asked for more

Really loved this teacher.  Very organized and easy to follow.  I was a mature student returning to school for first time.  Everything was clearly laid out and systematic. She is very helpful.  Tough but fair marker.  I took the required literature class with her too, and loved it.
Very sweet woman and an excellent prof! I had her for english first year! She is veyr helpful and the TA I had as well was helpful! Definitely take her class if you have the chance

She is awesome. She made a class about essay writing about as interesting and fun as it could have been. She gave really useful comments, and my essays are definitely better after having taken her class. Also, don't worry about her accent. I think some people were scared off because of it, but you get used to it by the end of the first class.

Only an amazing prof like Ms Sexton can make Canadian Lit interesting! She is adorable and cares highly for each student. She is a lenient marker but is useful, she teaches a lot of main concepts in easy to understand ways. TAKE ANYTHING SHE TEACHES!!!!
SIMPLY THE BEST,BEST, BEST PROF EVER!WHY DOESN'T SHE TEACH 3RD YEAR!!!!WHY??????

Melanie Sexton is possibly the best prof at Ottawa U.  The only downside is that after you're done her class, you'll be terminally depressed that cloning technology isn't advanced enough for her to teach every English course at the school.

Prof. Sexton was the only professor I had that cared about me and how I was doing. She likes to know her students names which makes it more personal and there is not one mean bone in her body. She wants the best for everyone.
I'm stalking the Rabaska pages to check if she's taking Mystery Novel this term -- had her for Can Lit and loved her. Wish she taught 3rd year+ courses :)

She is the most adorable professor ever! I was not to thrilled about canadian lit (I'm still not), but she tried her best to convey the literature the best way she could and make it fun! Take her class! She is a leniant marker too, and her comments are very helpful!

Excellent professor! Lectures are really interesting and kept my attention the full 3 hours. She really cares that you understand the course content and is very open to opinions different from hers. I would certainly take her class again!

I will take any class she teaches. She's funny and EASY TO PLEASE, just bring her your essay outline and she'll put you into her "this student planned essay therefore must give good mark" category. You'll get used to her voice after 3 sessions. After a year I hardly even remembered that she had a disability, she manages to communicate so fluidly.

This women is so sweet! So helpful, so enthusiastic about canadian lit. Makes a boring subject tolerable and somewhat interesting. DONT TAKE CANADAIN LIT WITH ANYONE ELSE. I respect her and admire her for being such a great teacher and being hearing impaired at the same time, it must be tough on her. WAY TO GO PROF SEXTON!

Amazing professor. She's nice, knows her stuff, really helpful and engaged with the students, actually wants to know our opinions on teaching methods and how to improve the class, doesn't take the material too seriously and doesn't get offended when students admit to hating the poetry :P Her voice is fine, when you get used to it you hardly notice.
No Comments
Great prof! Very nice lady. She really likes the material, and takes it personally if you don't. She asked us for suggestions on books that students would like better. Very helpful.

her voice is annoying but you have to respect her since she's deaf. class is boring but easy, good to take in 1st year just for the marks. if you already know anything about essays though, you won't learn anything new. overall very nice teacher, but it doesn't matter b/c you won't be going to class!

Even two years after taking this course I remember her as one of the most noteworthy profs I have had. She is a very smart and insightful woman and she picks good novels. Her ability to teach the class effectively despite being deaf was very inspiring. I highly recommend her courses.
No Comments
Vey nice prof.
She is very helpful and very nice.  You can tell she cares about what the students think.  She was able to move our exam from Dec. 22 to Dec. 6!!! For that alone, she's my hero!
Fair marker and quite helpful...but her screechy voice becomes unbearable halfway through the semester.
Excellent teacher, and fair marker. Tends to choose stories and novels with depressing or disturbing themes. However, she is interesting and her classes are well organized... work is well spaced out.
good sense of humour, interesting lectures, really great proff so far
she is so awesome and able to overcome her deafness to teach quite well
No Comments
